SIMPLE: undervalue
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undervalue
<hw>Un`der*val"ue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To value, rate, or estimate below the real worth; to
depreciate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To esteem lightly; to treat as of little worth; to
hold in mean estimation; to despise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In comparison of it I <qex>undervalued</qex> all ensigns of
authority.</q> <rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I write not this with the least intention to <qex>undervalue</qex>
the other parts of poetry.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undervalue</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Undervalue
<hw>Un`der*val"ue</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A low rate or price; a price
less than the real worth; undervaluation.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undervaluer</ent>⟦br⟧
